Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on modeling and simulating big data management systems (YARN) and big data programming models (MapReduce) within cloud computing environments, which falls under the scope of distributed and cluster computing. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper also discusses the integration and coordination of SDN-enabled networks with big data applications, which involves networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The simulation tool presented in the paper involves modeling and simulating complex systems (big data management systems and SDN-enabled networks) within cloud computing environments, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper briefly mentions the security implications of SDN-enabled networks, which may fall under the scope of cryptography and security. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The development of the simulation tool may involve software engineering principles and practices.
